Problems amending HomeSafe settings in My Account

Some TalkTalk customers are currently unable to amend their HomeSafe settings via My Account. Customers are able to log in to My Account without any issues, however, when they click the ‘Edit settings’ button for HomeSafe, the following error message is displayed: ‘Sorry, we had a problem updating your HomeSafe settings. Please try again later’.

1 of 5
Problems in the Gloucester area

Update 09:56 01/04 - Some customers in the Gloucester area are experiencing problems with the phone and broadband service. Traffic is being restored to emergency services first and then remaining services will be restored. If you are affected there is no need to call as engineers are already working to resolve the problems. We apologise for any inconvenience caused during this time.

2 of 5
Problems accessing Tiscali email account

Some customers may have issues accessing their Tiscali email accounts. Our engineers have identified that some email accounts may have been used to send large amounts of spam from our network.

3 of 5
Missing Sky boost and On Demand channels

Update 05/03 00:04 - Customers have reported that their Sky boost and On Demand channels are not appearing in the TalkTalk TV episode guide. This can be resolved with a manual update or by leaving the set top box overnight to automatically update.

4 of 5
Being aware of phone scams

Every year countless people are targeted by phone scammers and criminal organisations. Sadly this is a growing problem across all sectors. Here's some advice on how to stay safe.
